Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.50,0:00:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like only yesterday\NI was saving this place
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.81,0:00:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from being totally destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.62,0:00:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you guys remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.36,0:00:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You only mentioned it about\N15 times on the train here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.13,0:00:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and we never hear a peep\Nout of you about your exploits.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.23,0:00:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh. Point taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.43,0:00:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you all wanted to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.19,0:00:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't think it's\Ngoing to be that exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.61,0:00:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I pretty much just\Nhave to smile and wave
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.60,0:00:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as the dignitaries arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.06,0:00:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but you get to smile\Nand wave like a princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How exactly is that different\Nthan smiling and waving
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.93,0:00:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like, not a princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.11,0:00:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.57,0:00:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:00:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the long face?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.47,0:00:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just been feeling a little\Nunsure about things lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.22,0:01:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem that my\Nnew role as a princess
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.04,0:01:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,equates to all that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.50,0:01:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.56,0:01:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a real important\Nrole in Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.02,0:01:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Celestia wouldn't have\Nasked you to come today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.33,0:01:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if she didn't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.37,0:01:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.79,0:01:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.31,0:01:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now hurry along.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.44,0:01:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to risk\Nhaving that important role
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.43,0:01:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,diminished because you're tardy\Nfor your regal meet and greet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Duke and Duchess\Nof Mare-tonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.45,0:01:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That was it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Celestia had\Nyou come all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.42,0:01:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Crystal Empire\Njust to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.32,0:02:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, whoa, really\Nregal and important!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.46,0:02:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Subtitles by YayPonies\Nhttp://yayponies.eu{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.03,0:02:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for understanding our\Ndesire to keep the number
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of those privy to these\Nconfidential discussions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.21,0:02:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to a minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.19,0:02:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.85,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else I can\Ndo to assist with their visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.68,0:03:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Twilight, but\Ntheir visit is already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.97,0:03:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.10,0:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.79,0:03:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I just don't really\Nunderstand why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.47,0:03:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't one of the Royal Guard\Nhave unfurled the banner?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.03,0:03:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Having all four of us in\Nthe Empire to greet them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,lets the dignitaries\Nknow that their visit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.13,0:03:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is considered an important one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.54,0:03:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, it gives me\Nan opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.25,0:03:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to see my favorite\Nsister-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.68,0:03:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.35,0:03:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.00,0:03:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well, it's just that Princess{\i0}\N{\i1}Luna raises the moon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.31,0:03:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Princess Celestia{\i0}\N{\i1}raises the sun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You protect the Crystal Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And all I seem to do is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,smile and wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.12,0:04:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ It isn't that I'm ungrateful
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.17,0:04:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ For all the things {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.66,0:04:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ that I've earned {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ For all the journeys{\i0}\N{\i1}I have taken ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ All the lessons that{\i0}\N{\i1}I have learned ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.94,0:04:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ But I wonder where{\i0}\N{\i1}I'm going now ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.95,0:04:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ What my role is meant to be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.43,0:04:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I don't know how to travel {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.92,0:04:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ To a future that I can't see
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.60,0:04:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I have my wings {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I wear this crown {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ I'm a Princess this is true
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ But it's still{\i0}\N{\i1}unclear to me ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.74,0:04:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Just what I am meant to do {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.41,0:04:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I want to have a purpose {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.83,0:05:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Want to do all that I can {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.82,0:05:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I want to make{\i0}\N{\i1}a contribution ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.33,0:05:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I want to feel part{\i0}\N{\i1}of the plan ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Your destiny's uncertain {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.28,0:05:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ And that's sometimes{\i0}\N{\i1}hard to take ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.03,0:05:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ But it will become{\i0}\N{\i1}much clearer ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.66,0:05:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ With every new{\i0}\N{\i1}choice you make ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.67,0:05:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Patience is never easy {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I understand{\i0}\N{\i1}wanting more ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.94,0:05:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I know how hard{\i0}\N{\i1}it is to wait ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ To spread your{\i0}\N{\i1}wings and soar ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.64,0:05:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ But you stand{\i0}\N{\i1}here for a reason ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.89,0:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You are gifted{\i0}\N{\i1}and you are strong ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.53,0:05:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ That crown is upon your head
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.86,0:05:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Because you belong {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.18,0:05:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Know that your time {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.38,0:05:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ is coming soon {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ As the sun rises {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.64,0:06:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ So does the moon {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.41,0:06:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ As love finds a place {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.02,0:06:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ in every heart {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You are a princess {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You'll play your part {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ We understand{\i0}\N{\i1}you wanting more ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.79,0:06:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ A chance to shine {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ A chance to soar {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Soon will come the{\i0}\N{\i1}day it turns around ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.78,0:06:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Know that your time{\i0}\N{\i1}is coming soon ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.51,0:06:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ As the sun rises {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.94,0:06:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ So does the moon {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.98,0:06:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ As love finds a place {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.53,0:06:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ in every heart {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.84,0:06:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You are a princess {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.18,0:06:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You'll play your part {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.10,0:06:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You are a princess {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.58,0:06:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You'll play your part {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.53,0:06:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Your time will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.60,0:07:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.32,0:07:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You came out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.91,0:07:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he friend or is he\Nfoe, the pony wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.98,0:07:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can assure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I am no "friend".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.26,0:07:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Lord Tirek.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.14,0:07:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will take what should\Nhave been mine long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.36,0:08:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.14,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just had the\Nmost terrible dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think I'm here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.24,0:08:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You know as well as I that this\Nwas not a dream, but a vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.99,0:08:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we haven't much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.69,0:08:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The stronger he becomes, the\Nmore we are all in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.47,0:08:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tirek and his brother{\i0}\N{\i1}Scorpan came here{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from a distant land, intent on{\i0}\N{\i1}stealing Equestrian magic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.55,0:08:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Scorpan soon came to{\i0}\N{\i1}appreciate the ways{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.01,0:08:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of Equestria, even befriending{\i0}\N{\i1}a young unicorn wizard.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.89,0:08:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Scorpan urged his brother\N{\i1}to abandon their plans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.04,0:08:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When Tirek refused,{\i0}\N{\i1}Scorpan alerted us{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to Tirek's intentions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.23,0:08:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Scorpan returned to his own land,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.86,0:09:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and Tirek was sent to{\i0}\N{\i1}Tartarus for his crimes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But it appears he has\Nfound a way to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.45,0:09:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe it happened\Nwhen Cerberus
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.57,0:09:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,left his post at\Nthe gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.54,0:09:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.43,0:09:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is he just now\Nstarting to steal magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.93,0:09:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,His time in Tartarus\Nleft him very weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He has just now gained enough\Nstrength to use his dark powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.56,0:09:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But with each passing moment,\Nhe grows stronger still.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.96,0:09:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know just the\NPrincess who could stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.77,0:09:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I'll find him and--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.15,0:09:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, Twilight,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.87,0:09:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I must call on\Nanother to stop Tirek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.74,0:09:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As in Discord, Discord?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.63,0:09:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's\Nthat big of a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.21,0:09:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He can be very helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He can sense when there's a\Nmagical imbalance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.37,0:09:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The next time\NTirek steals magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.10,0:09:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Discord will be able\Nto track him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are you supposed\Nto do in the meantime?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.05,0:09:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless of course one of you\Nneeds me to smile and wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.19,0:10:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.88,0:10:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Castle of\Nthe Two Sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.94,0:10:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not really\Nneeded anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Might as well catch up\Non some of my reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.96,0:10:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You want some company?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.25,0:10:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been a while since\Nwe've visited the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.27,0:10:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Might be fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.70,0:10:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I could use a\Nlittle company right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.79,0:10:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I still can't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.93,0:10:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,we had to give\Nback the Elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.21,0:10:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It had to be done or the Tree of\NHarmony wouldn't have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.63,0:10:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But Twilight was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even without the Elements, our\Nfriendship is as strong as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.36,0:10:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope another\N"friend" of ours
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.84,0:10:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,never makes us sorry we\Nhad to give them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.30,0:10:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh ho!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.18,0:10:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking\Nabout me, I presume?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.28,0:10:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.68,0:10:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My ears were burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.16,0:10:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you even\Ndoing here, Discord?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.74,0:10:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Just a bit of light\Nreading before I head off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,on my extremely\Nimportant mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.71,0:10:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose you all know\Nthat I've been tapped
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.48,0:11:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to capture a\Ncertain escapee.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.87,0:11:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.21,0:11:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, Spike,\Nit is a "big deal".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.48,0:11:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems I possess a magic that\Ngives me quite an important role
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.30,0:11:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in Equestria.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.41,0:11:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they should make\Nme an Alicorn Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.17,0:11:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In your dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.09,0:11:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I never dream\Nof such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask Princess Luna.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.78,0:11:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you have a creepy\Nmagic-stealing villain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to track down?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.16,0:11:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.98,0:11:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that I couldn't help\Nbut notice that Twilight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't yet opened this\Nlittle chest of hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.34,0:11:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It got me thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.18,0:11:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What if what's locked inside is\Nsomething that could help her
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,prove her royal worth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.74,0:11:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I only bring it up because she\Nsaid that she'd been feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.66,0:11:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,like her role as a princess\Ndoesn't equate to much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know how\Nshe was feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.31,0:12:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.34,0:12:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Is eavesdropping not the way\Nyou're supposed to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.41,0:12:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what your best pals are up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.31,0:12:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Woe is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.86,0:12:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Will I ever learn the intricate\Nnuances of being a good friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.90,0:12:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahem!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.44,0:12:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in any case, I suppose\Nnow is as good a time as any
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.76,0:12:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to make my exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.45,0:12:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And good riddance!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.15,0:12:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oopsey doopsey,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost left with the little\Njournal you've all been keeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What a fascinating read.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.62,0:12:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't you girls\Njust learned so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.58,0:12:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I've bookmarked a few of the\Nmore interesting passages.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.84,0:12:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You really should take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.15,0:12:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're still on for tea later\Naren't we, Fluttershy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.80,0:12:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.54,0:12:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bring the\Ncucumber sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I think the "reformed"\NDiscord is more obnoxious
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.90,0:13:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,than the "before he\Nwas reformed" Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.67,0:13:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.75,0:13:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But he could be\Nright, couldn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What if there is something{\i0}\N{\i1}important in that chest?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one\Nway to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.35,0:13:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.86,0:13:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be something\Nin this library
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.63,0:13:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that can help me figure\Nout how to open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is in\None of these books.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.84,0:13:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I just know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:13:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tirek, I presume.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.50,0:14:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.87,0:14:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.04,0:14:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As a bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.43,0:14:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I commend you on\Nyour escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.62,0:14:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid the\Nfeeling isn't mutual.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.81,0:14:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have known you would\Nwant to have Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.55,0:14:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.87,0:14:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm not doing\Nthis for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.31,0:14:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing it for my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.31,0:14:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just between the two of us,\Nit's mostly for Fluttershy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.05,0:14:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.40,0:14:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not saying\Nyou're friends with...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.58,0:14:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponies!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.28,0:14:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.37,0:14:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I am surprised that someone with\Nyour intellect does not see
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this "friendship" is but a\Nnew form of imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.13,0:14:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly you've had to\Nabandon your true nature
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.73,0:14:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay in their good graces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.23,0:14:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I have done nothing of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.77,0:15:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. I've seen this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was always weak-minded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.05,0:15:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You are Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.68,0:15:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You are legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.17,0:15:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot fall into the same\Ntrap that claimed my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.19,0:15:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me to grow strong and be\Nrewarded with something
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,far greater than\Nfriendship...freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.16,0:15:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I have stripped these\Nponies of their magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.83,0:15:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing would give\Nme greater pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,than to see their world\Nturned upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.96,0:15:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Who better to do so than the\Nmaster of chaos himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.96,0:15:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Join me, Discord, and\Nreclaim your greatness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.52,0:15:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless, of course,\N"pony errand boy"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.38,0:15:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is the role you've always\Nwanted to play in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.28,0:16:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I've found something!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been reading our journal\Nand there's something
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.39,0:16:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting about the sections\Nthat Discord bookmarked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Applejack, do you remember\Nwhen you had to tell everypony
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that the tonic Granny bought\Nfrom the Flim-Flam brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't really work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.84,0:16:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was one of the hardest\Nthings I ever had to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.53,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to disappoint everypony,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.48,0:16:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's no way Granny\Ncould have made that dive
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.77,0:16:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because this tonic is a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But in that moment, I\Nknew had to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.05,0:16:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I just knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.31,0:16:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what that's got to do\Nwith opening the chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.45,0:16:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've found that each of you\Nhas had to face a situation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.24,0:16:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where living up to the\NElement of Harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.97,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you represent wasn't easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.05,0:16:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fluttershy, it was when you\Nrealized that the way to show
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.31,0:16:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,kindness to the Breezies was by\Nforcing them to leave your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.64,0:16:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The looks on their{\i0}\N{\i1}poor little faces.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.64,0:17:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I knew that as{\i0}\N{\i1}difficult as it was,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing them away was the\Nkindest thing I could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.22,0:17:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Rarity, even after Suri took\Nadvantage of your generosity
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.70,0:17:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at Fashion Week\Nin Manehattan,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.21,0:17:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you didn't let it cause you to{\i0}\N{\i1}abandon your generous spirit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.19,0:17:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I simply couldn't have\Nlived with myself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.11,0:17:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,if I didn't do something\Nspecial for the friends
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.94,0:17:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,who have always been\Nso generous to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.63,0:17:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainbow Dash, you had the chance\Nto fly with the Wonderbolts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.85,0:17:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Equestria Games
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.37,0:17:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead you chose to\Ncompete with your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. But being loyal to my\Nfriends was way ...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.06,0:17:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My turn! My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinkie Pie, you realized that\Nseeing your friend laugh
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.94,0:17:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was more important than proving\Nyou were a better party planner
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.56,0:17:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,than Cheese Sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.94,0:17:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Best party I've ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.17,0:17:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's clear we've all had our\Nmoments to shine, Twilight,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.25,0:17:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm with Applejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What does any of\Nthis have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.97,0:17:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with the opening of the chest?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.94,0:17:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you had tough\Nchoices to make,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but when you made the right{\i0}\N{\i1}one and embraced your Element,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.90,0:17:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it helped somepony else{\i0}\N{\i1}make the right choice too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:17:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each of you received{\i0}\N{\i1}something from the pony{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.85,0:18:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}whose life you helped change.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.25,0:18:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it sounds crazy, but\Nmaybe there's something special
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about those objects that could\Nlead us to the location
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.38,0:18:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.65,0:18:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The chest is connected\Nto the Tree of Harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.14,0:18:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tree is connected\Nto the Elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Elements are\Nconnected to all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.62,0:18:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be a connection!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.65,0:18:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to admit it,\Nbut maybe Discord
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.71,0:18:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,was trying to be a\Ngood friend after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.94,0:18:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything on them\Nthat would give us a clue
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.43,0:18:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as to where the keys might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.56,0:18:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just ordinary,\Neveryday objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.23,0:18:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Boneless!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.75,0:18:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Give us that key!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.07,0:18:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's\Ngoing to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.05,0:19:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still one key missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.00,0:19:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The key that represents\Nthe Element of Magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My Element.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.10,0:19:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I'm sure that if\Nwe've gotten our keys,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.64,0:19:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you have too, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.88,0:19:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Think, Twilight! When have you\Ncompleted a difficult magical
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.96,0:19:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,task and in doing so encouraged\Nanother pony to do the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.05,0:19:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.14,0:19:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If I had, I would have written\Nabout it in the Journal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.06,0:19:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Twilight, I'm sure\Nyou'll get your key eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.52,0:19:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.71,0:19:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That I'm needed in\NCanterlot at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I came as quickly as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.05,0:19:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.13,0:19:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it Tirek?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.31,0:19:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I am afraid I put too\Nmuch trust in Discord
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.06,0:19:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the effect that friendship\Nwould have upon him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:20:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Discord has betrayed{\i0}\N{\i1}the ponies of Equestria{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.96,0:20:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and joined forces with Tirek.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How could he do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.62,0:20:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought our friendship\Nmeant something to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.01,0:20:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought he had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.96,0:20:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Tirek has stolen enough magic\Nthat he now has the strength
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to steal flight as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.44,0:20:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Without Pegasi to\Ncontrol the weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there will be no{\i0}\N{\i1}rain in Equestria.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There is word he has gone{\i0}\N{\i1}after earth ponies as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.70,0:20:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Without their strength,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they will not be able{\i0}\N{\i1}to tend the land.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.91,0:20:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponies will no longer be\Nin control of their world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.76,0:20:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That power will\Nbelong solely to Tirek.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:21:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no doubt that Tirek\Nis after alicorn magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,With Discord by his side,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.74,0:21:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we will not be able to\Nstop him from taking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.47,0:21:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it is in his possession,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.34,0:21:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,his power will know no bounds\Nand all hope will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.53,0:21:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is one solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.14,0:21:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It is only by making\Nthis sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.66,0:21:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that Equestria and the lands\Nbeyond it might be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.37,0:21:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We must rid ourselves\Nof our magic
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.98,0:21:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,before Tirek has the chance\Nto steal it from us.
